I‚Äôd second this also for `LocationContext`. My use case was for a component that needed to know if it was inside a Router or not. For example, a hook that would let us know that:

```js
import { LocationContext } from 'react-router'

// Hook that returns true if component rendered inside of LocationContext.Provider
export function useIsInRouter() {
  return !!React.useContext(LocationContext);
}
```

As far as I can tell, this is not currently possible with v6.0.0-alpha.2, because the contexts aren‚Äôt exported directly and the existing hooks will error if used outside of the necessary context providers.

(This does rely a little on the implementation detail that `LocationContext` is created without a default value, so maybe there‚Äôs a better way?)
